Description: Fragment of sub-round handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine red-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Agoranax. Unlikely to be equated witha piece drawn by Pettie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 31, 6). From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0327.08.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0706)
